The United Niger Delta Energy Development Security Strategy (UNDEDSS) has called on stakeholders in the region to stop blackmailing the Minister of the Niger Delta, Senator Godswill Akpabio; the Interim Management Council of the Niger Delta Development Commission (NDDC), as presently constituted; and Chairman of the Niger Delta Amnesty Committee, Professor Charles Dokubo. Rising from its yearly general meeting in Warri, yesterday, Secretary General of the organisation, Mr. Tony Uranta, said some disgruntled elements in the region and Abuja are attempting to keep the Niger Delta steeped in corruption and underdevelopment. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .